---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About — Baji Tumendemberel" current="about">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-24">
    <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-accent mb-6">About</p>
    <h1 class="font-display text-5xl md:text-7xl leading-none mb-12">
      Nice to meet you.
    </h1>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[200px_1fr] gap-10 items-start">
      <div class="aspect-square w-40 md:w-full rounded-full bg-neutral-900 border border-white/10 overflow-hidden">
        <!-- Replace with real portrait when ready -->
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-lg text-white/80 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          My name is Baji Tumendemberel. I graduated from Yale University in 2022. I find my
          passion at the intersection between data science and social justice.
        </p>
        <p>
          My work focuses on the questions that lawyers, advocates, and policymakers can't
          answer with intuition alone — questions about disparate outcomes, structural
          barriers, and who gets counted (or doesn't) in the data we make decisions on. I
          gravitate toward projects where statistical evidence can shift a legal argument,
          shape a policy debate, or sharpen a public conversation.
        </p>
        <p>
          I work primarily in Python and R, with detours into SQL, GIS tooling, and whatever
          court-records scraper a given project requires. I'm always open to conversations
          about civil-rights litigation, public-interest data journalism, and computational
          social science — feel free to reach out.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
